</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukarlithas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karlithas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/8/02 11:10:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1507.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There are many ways ..</span><hr size=1> In my opinion, true neutrality is self contradicting at best. <br>
<br>
It is frowned up if someone kill animals, but it is perfectly reasonable if the purpose was to satisfy one¡¦s hunger.<br>
<br>
It is bad to tilt the balance of good and evil, but it is perfectly acceptable to strike down a person (despite his alignment) if he is caught ¡§disrupting the balance of nature¡¨<br>
<br>
It is unacceptable to chop down a tree, but it is perfectly logical if the woods are used to build shelter for oneself.<br>
<br>
All of them are contradicting principles.  It is not right to do something unless it is justified by personal need.  It is ¡§need¡¨ that drives the idea of neutrality.   A true neutral aligned individual would not side with either good or evil unless he has the ¡§need¡¨ for it.  An animal should not be killed unless there is a ¡§need¡¨ for it.  A tree should not be chopped down unless there is a ¡§need¡¨ for it.  In simple words, whatever a true neutral aligned individual does is driven solely by his ¡§need¡¨.  <br>
<br>
What is this need?  It's basic animal instinct.  Both good and evil aligned have ideologies that they try to fulfill.  The patterns of their actions are already settled forth by their religion, society, culture, and their environment.  Yet neutrals care not of these ideologies and their actions are only responses to the situation at hand.  Frankly, it is selfishness that is the driving force behind those of neutral aligned individuals.  Self perseverance and self fulfillment are the reasons behind a true neutral¡¦s actions.  <br>
<br>
As a druid, myself, I don't question my neutrality over the war with the Crushbone orcs.  It is simply justified by my own selfish attempt to preserve my own life.  It is rather simple ¡V if an orc wishes me dead, I have every right to ally myself with enemies of the orcs and defend myself.  It is this belief that made me an ally of dragons and dwarves on Velious as well.  Simple, the first race that wished me dead on Velious was the giants, and the result is that my alliance with the dragons and the dwarves.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueliezeroferudin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 346<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/8/02 2:58:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1507.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There are many ways ..</span><hr size=1> Also, consider that Alignment is supposed to a Guide, an /inclination/ your character has...  Do you lean towards Good, Bad, or indifferent?  Do you respect Authority and Law, or do you bristle at the thought of being manipulated in any form?<br>
<br>
Alignment is not like some absolute distinction you choose and follow like it was a Political Party or something.  It also isn't something that is stamped on your forehead.  People make assumptions all the time, and have various and sundry prejudices.  Alignment is something that is only discernable through careful observation and knowledge of a person. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.alienexplorer.com/clipart/images5/wolf.pawprint2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 279<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/8/02 4:28:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1507.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There are many ways ..</span><hr size=1> Wow, lotta good stuff before I ever got to it.  Not much time (as always lately), so here's...<br>
